<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_2e8b0f77-9f25-4a76-bc41-d1780fb8d720" outputclass="ncc-clause" variation="SA"><sptc>B6D2</sptc><title id="_f9fcd99a-3f7a-4eae-b763-f225b67c28ce">General requirements</title><archive-num>2019: SA B1.4(1) and (2)</archive-num><subclause id="_daff8341-c171-4a0e-8457-10754cdcad03" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_385fc354-7bea-4842-b72c-d78d350e92fd">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>A <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1422_4.4.0.xml#_bd764954-3054-4109-81f2-164feefc5058" id="_e406c831-c37f-439a-985c-aa9f7d64eabb" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">rainwater service</xref> must comply with Section 15 of AS/NZS 3500.1 with the following variation—</p><p>(d) For <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/2526_1.10.0.xml#_aaefaaca-c6f4-4f31-b202-f2866a59e6ac" id="_7c120cba-edfe-4d74-998a-9b12929fbc84" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">Class 1</xref> buildings and extensions or additions to <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/2526_1.10.0.xml#_aaefaaca-c6f4-4f31-b202-f2866a59e6ac" id="_b49f8429-ce4f-4561-a6b2-fa88a1696fa0" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">Class 1</xref> buildings the following applies. </p><p>Where a drinking water is used to top-up a rainwater tank or supplement a rainwater service, it shall be maintained by an automatic change-over device, automatic top-up device or a device/mechanism that facilitates an automatic switching without manual intervention.</p></subclause></clause>